    <item>
      <title>Re: Gear Gap Between Raiders and Casuals Too Wide</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=229350#M229350</link>
      <description>In my opinion there is absolutely nothing wrong with wide gear gap between raiders and casuals.  However, what is wrong is that the casuals eventually can not perform their job because of the gear gap.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For example, you casuals are probably all excited over the Arcstone quest armor, but sadly those are no better than what I got during PLANE OF POWER expansion.  And that is the best you could get for casuals, armor that is 4-5 expansions old (I forgot how old, all I remember is thinking back it was such a waste of time doing those due to what I got now).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What is also sad is you could not possibly survive well given the kind of armor then.  If you are elemental geared, then your HP and AC will suffer greatly compared to others, you are not doing any of the new missions specifically DoDH stuff.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I don't know what kind of gear you could get now, by looking at the current quests such as the Relic ones with ring etc they seen quite nice, but the armor for tanks severely made it hard for casuals to do content such as 68, 69, 70 spell missions in DoDH.  (I am sure you can do some of them until you hit a brick wall with a certain 2k hitter boss or hard trash).  And what is sad for the situation is that there's absolutely nothing you can do about it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Now, I am assuming casuals don't raid, they log on play a couple of hours in low end zones get maybe 1-2aa, then log off, doing so maybe 3-4 times a week.  With raiders, if you cant do an encounter, just keep raiding, get more gears and raid better encounters.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What if casuals can not do a group encounter due to lack of gears eg: 70.1 70.2 missions ? nothing you can do at all.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What the developers are doing is trying to make raid trash (1-2k hitters) and put them into group trash so that raiders will have a challenge when doing these, I say keep the raid trash where they belong and make group encounters easier.  (I know there is already normal and hard setting for most, but normal really still needs to be toned down for most of us especially 70.1 and 70.2)&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
