      <title>Re: Gear Gap Between Raiders and Casuals Too Wide</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=230348#M230348</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Good point Jaya. It is something that the top tier raiders forget all the time. Progressing with group gear is a lot harder than progressing with top raid gear. I remember how easy the MPG trials seemed when I was doing them with top tier folks from TR. Over a year later, I did the MPG trials again with casual players and they were a lot harder. On the other hand, the gear was a lot more of an upgrade for most of them. This is the mechanism I would like to see used by casual players to catch up (or simply stay in the game). The encounters should be more challenging for them but the rewards are much better.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Another thing I think that the top tier raiders are forgetting is that it is in their own best interests to keep the gear gap between casual and raiders closer than it currently is. You should want guild applicants that are not totaly gimp unless you plan to only poach from other raiding guilds.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
