&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Here's an introduction to the human race.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;People talk about the same things over and over again.&amp;nbsp; They talk about the weather, their jobs, politics, and their hobbies, over and over again.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The same old same old stories (boy meets girl, shoot em up, family stories, kid cartoons) happen on TV or movies with little variations, again and again.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Dear Abby type columns have the same 12 or so questions, ad infinitum.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Then, when that show / movie / hobby / column, etc... is over, they restart a new one, different title, but same content... all...over... again.&amp;nbsp; This is for the majority of people, hate them for being repetitive all you wish.&amp;nbsp; Wouldn't happen so often in every aspect of life (games, TV, movies, entertainment) if it was just 1-2 isolated people, now would it?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;So, people like to talk about the same thing, and start new threads, (God forbid, end of the world, sigh), about the same old topics, which is NO different, than talking about the weather, tomorrow, just like today, cuz guess what?&amp;nbsp; It's STILL hot.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Ditto with the same old concerns since Classic EQ, and the same old threads, about the same old topics.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;So, good luck on that human race rehabilitation project, or application to Board Police / Board Mod status, or whatever you get your jollies from.&amp;nbsp; Me?&amp;nbsp; I'll sit here, and be totally ok and unsurprised that another topic happens JUST UNDER another topic of the same kind.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
